Location:  Singapore
Business Development Manager – Singapore
Our client, a multinational company – specializing high performance industrial and motor oils and lubricants, is looking for a Business Development Manager to join their growing team.
The successful Business Development Manager would have at least 4 years of oils or lubricants sales experience across SEA or APAC, preferably dealing automotive workshops or distributors across the region. The Business Development Manager would be responsible for the sales across the region, with the focus of Malaysia market.
The Business Development Manager would be the managing the distributors and workshops. This is a newly created role for the region, hence we are looking for a highly responsible and independent individual to join the client.
If you are available and interested in this position and would like further information please forward your CV for immediate consideration to
kierra.foocv@amoriabond.com
Amoria Bond operates as an employment agency and employment business. No terminology in this advert is intended to discriminate on the grounds of age, and we confirm that we are happy to accept applications from persons of any age for this role.
